        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 7:03PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 703 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Brownson to 6 miles east of Pawnee
Buttes, or extending from 8 miles northwest of Sidney to 30 miles
south of Kimball, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Peetz, Westplains and Pawnee Buttes.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rain is occurring with these storms and may lead to flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.

Prepare for sudden gusty winds. Secure loose objects and move to a
safe shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
